luxurious /lʌɡˈzjʊərɪəs/

ADJ If you describe something as luxurious , you mean that it is very comfortable and expensive. 豪华的 

例： Our honeymoon was two days in Las Vegas at a luxurious hotel called Le Mirage. 我们的蜜月为期两天，是在拉斯维加斯一家名为“幻影”的豪华酒店度过的。 

2. luxuriously ADV 豪华地 

例： The dining-room is luxuriously furnished and carpeted. 餐厅里的家具和地毯非常豪华。 

3. ADJ Luxurious means feeling or expressing great pleasure and comfort. 心情舒畅的 

例： Amy tilted her wine in her glass with a luxurious sigh. 埃米把杯中的葡萄酒斜向一边，适意地叹了口气。 

4. luxuriously ADV 心情舒畅地 [ADV after v] 

例： Liz laughed, stretching luxuriously. 莉兹一边大笑，一边心情舒畅地伸了个懒腰。

</div>

